OL,3,COne in six infections now resistant to
OL,4,Cantibiotics, WHO warns
OL,6,FThe report identifies eight common
OL,7,Fbacteria that can cause disease -
OL,8,Fincluding E. coli, Klebsiella
OL,9,Fpneumoniae, and Staphylococcus aureus
OL,10,F- as key contributors to resistant
OL,11,Finfections in the urinary tract,
OL,12,Fbloodstream, gastrointestinal system
OL,13,Fand cases of gonorrhoea.
OL,15,FBacteria known as 'gram negative',
OL,16,Fparticularly E. coli and K.
OL,17,Fpneumoniae, are posing the greatest
OL,18,Fthreat.
